# AI_WAY_OF_BUILDING_V1 — .gitignore
#
# The kit is mostly markdown (canonical docs + cycle definitions) + bash hooks +
# TOML FSMs + Claude Code config. It does not host runtime code; what gets
# ignored here is OS junk, editor scratch, backup files from sed operations,
# and per-user Claude Code settings.
#
# Files that LOOK like they should be ignored but ARE COMMITTED (per kit
# discipline — see DASHBOARD.md §2.5):
#   - HANDOVER.md (kit-level session lineage; the deep-night-3 false-claim fix
#     established that this IS committed)
#   - SHADOW_PASS_*.md (SHD cycle preservation artifacts)
#   - threat-model.md (per-project security verdict-delta record)
#   - All CHARTER.md / DESIGN.md / STATUS.md / TODO.md / ADR-*.md / RUNBOOK.md

# ── OS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
.AppleDouble
.LSOverride
._*
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# ── Editors / IDEs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
.cursor/
.zed/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.*.un~
.netrwhist

# ── Backup / temp files (from sed -i.bak, editor saves, etc.) ──────
*.bak
*.tmp
*.orig
*.rej

# ── Claude Code per-user state ─────────────────────────────────────
# settings.json is committed (shared kit config);
# settings.local.json is per-user (overrides + per-user permissions)
.claude/settings.local.json

# ── Secrets (defensive — the secret-scan hook is the primary defense
#    but git-level exclusion is belt-and-suspenders) ────────────────
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
credentials.json
credentials.yaml
secrets.json
secrets.yaml

# ── Logs (when generated by hook test runs or CI) ──────────────────
# Specific log files; .log extension is exempt from vocabulary-lint per the
# kit's own exemption list, so the convention is logs ARE committed when they
# are documentation. Runtime logs in dedicated directories are ignored.
logs/
*.log.gz

# ── Worktrees / git internals ──────────────────────────────────────
# git-managed; should never appear in ignore but listed defensively
.git/
*.lock

# ── Documentation build artifacts (if any tool generates from .md) ─
_site/
.docusaurus/
.cache/
public/
